Messages may not be processed if, for instance, the message contents could not be deserialized due to an incompatible schema. Alternately, a consumed messages may not have been produced, hence being effectively dropped. Such messages would also be counted toward the error rate.

num-persistent-queries.desc: The current number of persistent queries running in this engine

CREATED-queries.desc: Count of queries in CREATED state.

messages-consumed-total.desc: The total number of messages consumed across all queries

messages-consumed-per-sec.desc: The number of messages consumed per second across all queries

messages-produced-per-sec.desc: The number of messages produced per second across all queries

ERROR-queries.desc: Count of queries in ERROR state.

RUNNING-queries.desc: Count of queries in RUNNING state.

NOT_RUNNING-queries.desc: Count of queries in NOT_RUNNING state.

bytes-consumed-total.desc: The total number of bytes consumed across all queries

REBALANCING-queries.desc: Count of queries in REBALANCING state.

PENDING_SHUTDOWN-queries.desc: Count of queries in PENDING_SHUTDOWN state.

num-active-queries.desc: The current number of active queries running in this engine
